Progress: 0% Complete**\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ## References\n71: \n72: - Design: `changes/AR-031/design.md`\n73: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md`\n74: - Proposal: `changes/AR-031/proposal.md`\n75: - [TO BE FILLED: Add relevant references]\n\n(End of file - total 75 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-031 — RBAC 配置 |\n| Module | `manifests` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-0 pending] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: [TO BE FILLED]\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: [TO BE FILLED]\n  - Purpose: [TO BE FILLED]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775884703638,"end":1775884703654}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884703657,"sessionID":"ses_285064a34ffeQXA6kTt14U3nZx","part":{"id":"prt_d7afa1420001C953scC7U1EaEV","messageID":"msg_d7af9f5cd001wH9uHp3Aywenmf","sessionID":"ses_285064a34ffeQXA6kTt14U3nZx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-881815a813ba44c082d2e5e02e199db1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-030 |\n8: | Module | manifests |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: Define the official Helm Chart for AgentCube deployment, providing parameterized Kubernetes manifests for all core components. The Helm Chart enables:\n17: \n18: 1. **One-command Deployment**: Install AgentCube stack with `helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base`\n19: 2. **Configuration Flexibility**: Customize deployment via `values.yaml` (image registry, replicas, resources, Redis settings)\n20: 3. **Environment Adaptability**: Support dev/staging/prod environments through values overrides\n21: 4. **Component Isolation**: Deploy router, workloadmanager, agentd, Redis independently via subcharts or enabled flags\n22: \n23: **Components to be templated**:\n24: \n25: | Component | Kind | Purpose |\n26: |-----------|------|---------|\n27: | `workloadmanager` | Deployment + Service | Workload manager HTTP server (port 8080) |\n28: | `router` | Deployment + Service | Session routing reverse proxy (port 8080) |\n29: | `agentd` | Deployment | Idle cleanup controller with leader election |\n30: | `redis` | Deployment + Service | Session store (Redis 7 or Valkey) |\n31: | RBAC | ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding | Router and WorkloadManager permissions |\n32: | Secrets | Secret | JWT signing key, identity secret for picod auth |\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n37: \n38: ### 2.1 In Scope\n39: \n40: | Deliverable | Description |\n41: |-------------|-------------|\n42: | `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Chart metadata (name, version, appVersion, dependencies) |\n43: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Default values for all components |\n44: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager-deployment.yaml` | WorkloadManager Deployment template |\n45: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager-service.yaml` | WorkloadManager Service template (port 8080) |\n46: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-deployment.yaml` | Router Deployment template |\n47: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-service.yaml` | Router Service template (port 8080) |\n48: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-rbac.yaml` | ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding for router |\n49: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentd-deployment.yaml` | Agentd Deployment template with leader election |\n50: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-deployment.yaml` | Redis/Valkey Deployment template |\n51: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-service.yaml` | Redis Service template (port 6379) |\n52: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/jwt-secret.yaml` | JWT signing key Secret template |\n53: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/identity-secret.yaml` | Picod-Router identity Secret template |\n54: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Template helpers (name, labels, image helpers) |\n55: \n56: ### 2.2 Values Schema\n57: \n58: | Section | Key | Default | Description |\n59: |---------|-----|---------|-------------|\n60: | `global` | `imageRegistry` | `\"\"` | Global image registry override |\n61: | `global` | `imagePullSecrets` | `[]` | Global image pull secrets |\n62: | `workloadmanager` | `enabled` | `true` | Enable WorkloadManager deployment |\n63: | `workloadmanager.image` | `repository` | `workloadmanager` | Image repository |\n64: | `workloadmanager.image` | `tag` | `latest` | Image tag |\n65: | `workloadmanager.image` | `pullPolicy` | `IfNotPresent` | Image pull policy |\n66: | `workloadmanager` | `replicas` | `1` | Deployment replicas |\n67: | `workloadmanager` | `resources` | `{}` | Resource requests/limits |\n68: | `workloadmanager` | `env` | `[]` | Extra environment variables |\n69: | `workloadmanager.service` | `type` | `ClusterIP` | Service type |\n70: | `workloadmanager.service` | `port` | `8080` | Service port |\n71: | `router` | `enabled` | `true` | Enable Router deployment |\n72: | `router.image` | `repository` | `agentcube-router` | Image repository |\n73: | `router.image` | `tag` | `latest` | Image tag |\n74: | `router` | `replicas` | `1` | Deployment replicas |\n75: | `router` | `maxConcurrent` | `1000` | Max concurrent requests |\n76: | `router.rbac` | `create` | `true` | Create RBAC resources |\n77: | `router.serviceAccountName` | `agentcube-router` | ServiceAccount name |\n78: | `router.service` | `type` | `ClusterIP` | Service type |\n79: | `router.service` | `port` | `8080` | Service port |\n80: | `agentd` | `enabled` | `true` | Enable Agentd deployment |\n81: | `agentd.image` | `repository` | `agentd` | Image repository |\n82: | `agentd.image` | `tag` | `latest` | Image tag |\n83: | `agentd` | `idleThreshold` | `30m` | Idle cleanup threshold |\n84: | `agentd` | `checkInterval` | `5m` | Cleanup check interval |\n85: | `agentd` | `leaderElection` | `true` | Enable leader election |\n86: | `agentd` | `leaderElectionID` | `agentcube-agentd` | Leader election ID |\n87: | `redis` | `enabled` | `true` | Enable Redis deployment |\n88: | `redis.image` | `repository` | `redis` | Image repository (redis or valkey) |\n89: | `redis.image` | `tag` | `7-alpine` | Image tag |\n90: | `redis` | `passwordRequired` | `false` | Require Redis password |\n91: | `redis` | `password` | `\"\"` | Redis password (empty = no auth) |\n92: | `redis.service` | `port` | `6379` | Redis service port |\n93: | `jwt` | `secretName` | `agentcube-jwt-key` | JWT secret name |\n94: | `jwt` | `keyNamespace` | `agentcube` | Namespace for JWT secret |\n95: \n96: ### 2.3 Out of Scope\n97: \n98: | Item | Reason |\n99: |------|--------|\n100: | CRD installation | CRDs installed separately via agent-sandbox release assets |\n101: | Sandbox Pod templates | Dynamic creation by WorkloadManager, not static Helm template |\n102: | HorizontalPodAutoscaler | Not in initial scope; scale via replicas value |\n103: | Ingress resources | Network ingress handled separately per environment |\n104: | PersistentVolumeClaims | Redis uses ephemeral storage by default; PVC optional |\n105: | NetworkPolicies | Environment-specific; not in base chart |\n106: | Prometheus ServiceMonitor | Monitoring stack installed separately |\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n111: \n112: ### 3.1 新增文件\n113: \n114: | File | Description |\n115: |------|-------------|\n116: | `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Helm Chart metadata file |\n117: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Default configuration values |\n118: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager-deployment.yaml` | WorkloadManager Deployment template |\n119: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager-service.yaml` | WorkloadManager Service template |\n120: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-deployment.yaml` | Router Deployment template |\n121: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-service.yaml` | Router Service template |\n122: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-rbac.yaml` | Router RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) |\n123: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentd-deployment.yaml` | Agentd Deployment template |\n124: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-deployment.yaml` | Redis Deployment template |\n125: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-service.yaml` | Redis Service template |\n126: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/jwt-secret.yaml` | JWT signing key Secret template |\n127: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/identity-secret.yaml` | Picod-Router identity Secret template |\n128: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Named template helpers |\n129: \n130: ### 3.2 修改文件\n131: \n132: | File | Change |\n133: |------|--------|\n134: | N/A | No modifications required (pure addition) |\n135: \n136: ### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n137: \n138: | Dependency | Purpose |\n139: |------------|---------|\n140: | `Helm 3` | Template rendering and release management |\n141: | `Kubernetes 1.24+` | API versions for Deployment, Service, RBAC resources |\n142: | `agent-sandbox CRDs` | Required for WorkloadManager sandbox operations |\n143: | `docker images` | Pre-built images for router, workloadmanager, agentd, picod |\n144: \n145: ### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n146: \n147: | Consumer | Usage |\n148: |----------|-------|\n149: | `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` | `helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base` with values overrides |\n150: | `GitHub Actions (e2e.yml)` | E2E test workflow uses Helm chart for Kind cluster deployment |\n151: | `Production deployments` | `helm install` with environment-specific values files |\n152: | `CI/CD pipeline` | `build-push-release.yml` pushes images referenced by chart values |\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n157: \n158: ### Alternative 1: Static Kubernetes manifests (no Helm)\n159: \n160: **Approach**: Provide static YAML files in `manifests/` directory without templating.\n161: \n162: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n163: |--------|------------|\n164: | Pros | No Helm dependency; simpler for single-environment deployment |\n165: | Cons | No parameterization; requires manual edits per environment; no release management; no rollback support |\n166: \n167: **Decision**: Rejected. Helm provides essential parameterization, release tracking, and rollback capabilities for production deployments.\n168: \n169: ### Alternative 2: Kustomize overlays\n170: \n171: **Approach**: Use Kustomize with base manifests and environment overlays.\n172: \n173: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n174: |--------|------------|\n175: | Pros | Native kubectl support; declarative overlays; GitOps-friendly |\n176: | Cons | No release history; no rollback; no hook support; requires multiple overlay directories |\n177: \n178: **Decision**: Rejected. Helm provides better release management and is already used in E2E tests (`run_e2e.sh`). Kustomize could be added later for GitOps workflows.\n179: \n180: ### Alternative 3: Operator pattern for all components\n181: \n182: **Approach**: Deploy all components via a custom Kubernetes Operator.\n183: \n184: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n185: |--------|------------|\n186: | Pros | Full lifecycle management; reconciliation; CRD-based configuration |\n187: | Cons | High complexity; longer development time; agentd already uses controller-runtime pattern |\n188: \n189: **Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. Agentd uses controller-runtime; other components are simpler HTTP servers. Operator pattern adds unnecessary complexity for Deployment/Service management.\n190: \n191: ### Alternative 4: Multiple separate charts (one per component)\n192: \n193: **Approach**: Create independent Helm charts for each component (router-chart, workloadmanager-chart, agentd-chart, redis-chart).\n194: \n195: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n196: |--------|------------|\n197: | Pros | Independent versioning; selective deployment; clear ownership |\n198: | Cons | Complex dependency management; more release coordination; shared helpers duplicated |\n199: \n200: **Decision**: Rejected. AgentCube components are tightly integrated; single chart with `enabled` flags provides cleaner deployment experience. Subchart structure could be added later if needed.\n201: \n202: ### Alternative 5: Include CRDs in Helm chart\n203: \n204: **Approach**: Bundle agent-sandbox CRDs in Helm chart `crds/` directory.\n205: \n206: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n207: |--------|------------|\n208: | Pros | One-command full installation; no separate CRD step |\n209: | Cons | CRDs from external project (agent-sandbox); version mismatch risk; E2E uses separate download |\n210: \n211: **Decision**: Rejected. CRDs come from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` releases. Keeping CRDs separate aligns with E2E workflow (`kubectl apply` from GitHub releases). Chart focuses on AgentCube-specific deployments.\n212: \n213: ---\n214: \n215: ## 5. Risks\n216: \n217: | Risk | Mitigation |\n218: |------|------------|\n219: | Image registry mismatch | `global.imageRegistry` value allows registry override; defaults work for local Kind |\n220: | RBAC permission scope too broad | ClusterRole grants minimal permissions (Pod, Secret, TokenReview, CRD access); namespace-scoped option in values |\n221: | Redis password exposure | Default `passwordRequired=false`; production should set password via Secret reference |\n222: | Leader election deadlock | Agentd uses controller-runtime leader election with proper timeouts; single replica default avoids split-brain |\n223: | Helm template syntax errors | `_helpers.tpl` tested via `helm template` command; E2E validates rendered manifests |\n224: | Missing namespace | `--create-namespace` in E2E; explicit namespace in values for production |\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n229: \n230: - [ ] Create `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` with metadata\n231: - [ ] Create `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` with default configuration\n232: - [ ] Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` with named templates\n233: - [ ] Implement `workloadmanager-deployment.yaml` template\n234: - [ ] Implement `workloadmanager-service.yaml` template\n235: - [ ] Implement `router-deployment.yaml` template with Redis address env\n236: - [ ] Implement `router-service.yaml` template\n237: - [ ] Implement `router-rbac.yaml` with ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding\n238: - [ ] Implement `agentd-deployment.yaml` template with leader election\n239: - [ ] Implement `redis-deployment.yaml` template\n240: - [ ] Implement `redis-service.yaml` template\n241: - [ ] Implement `jwt-secret.yaml` template\n242: - [ ] Implement `identity-secret.yaml` template\n243: - [ ] Add `enabled` conditionals for each component template\n244: - [ ] Add resource limits/requests templates\n245: - [ ] Add liveness/readiness probe templates\n246: - [ ] Validate chart with `helm lint manifests/charts/base`\n247: - [ ] Test template rendering with `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base`\n248: - [ ] Update E2E script to use new chart structure if needed\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ## 7. References\n253: \n254: - ci-cd/design.md — E2E Helm usage (`manifests/charts/base` path, values examples)\n255: - design.md — Deployment model (Router, WorkloadManager, Agentd architecture)\n256: - sandbox-orchestration/design.md — Component configuration (flags, defaults)\n257: - Helm 3 Documentation — Chart structure, templates, values\n258: - Kubernetes API Reference — Deployment, Service, RBAC resource schemas\n259: - `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` — CRD requirements for WorkloadManager\n\n(End of file - total 259 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-030 |\n| Module | manifests |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | L |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nDefine the official Helm Chart for AgentCube deployment, providing parameterized Kubernetes manifests for all core components. The Helm Chart enables:\n\n1. **One-command Deployment**: Install AgentCube stack with `helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base`\n2. **Configuration Flexibility**: Customize deployment via `values.yaml` (image registry, replicas, resources, Redis settings)\n3. **Environment Adaptability**: Support dev/staging/prod environments through values overrides","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775884703640,"end":1775884703656}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884703668,"sessionID":"ses_285064a34ffeQXA6kTt14U3nZx","part":{"id":"prt_d7afa1779001u1YS7kR3kjW0H6","messageID":"msg_d7af9f5cd001wH9uHp3Aywenmf","sessionID":"ses_285064a34ffeQXA6kTt14U3nZx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-bd396d06d85b4d12ab5324970c410f01","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/values.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/values.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: imagePullSecrets: []\n2: nameOverride: \"\"\n3: fullnameOverride: \"\"\n4: \n5: redis:\n6:   addr: \"\"\n7:   password: \"\"\n8: \n9: workloadmanager:\n10:   replicas: 1\n11:   image:\n12:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager\n13:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n14:     tag: latest\n15:   service:\n16:     type: ClusterIP\n17:     port: 8080\n18:   resources:\n19:     limits:\n20:       cpu: 500m\n21:       memory: 512Mi\n22:     requests:\n23:       cpu: 100m\n24:       memory: 128Mi\n25:   extraEnv: []\n26: \n27: router:\n28:   replicas: 1\n29:   image:\n30:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router\n31:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n32:     tag: latest\n33:   service:\n34:     type: ClusterIP\n35:     port: 8080\n36:     targetPort: 8080\n37:   resources:\n38:     limits:\n39:       cpu: 500m\n40:       memory: 512Mi\n41:     requests:\n42:       cpu: 100m\n43:       memory: 128Mi\n44:   config: {}\n45:   extraEnv: []\n46:   serviceAccountName: \"\"\n47:   rbac:\n48:     create: false\n49: \n50: volcano:\n51:   scheduler:\n52:     enabled: false\n53:     replicas: 1\n54:     image:\n55:       repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler\n56:       pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n57:       tag: latest\n\n(End of file - total 57 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"imagePullSecrets: []\nnameOverride: \"\"\nfullnameOverride: \"\"\n\nredis:\n  addr: \"\"\n  password: \"\"\n\nworkloadmanager:\n  replicas: 1\n  image:\n    repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager\n    pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n    tag: latest\n  service:\n    type: ClusterIP\n    port: 8080\n  resources:\n    limits:\n      cpu: 500m","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/values.yaml","time":{"start":1775884703642,"end":1775884703666}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775884703689,"sessionID":"ses_285064a34ffeQXA6kTt14U3nZx","part":{"id":"prt_d7afa17b3001YZ1FCVCeb9H044","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7af9f5cd001wH9uHp3Aywenmf","sessionID":"ses_285064a34ffeQXA6kTt14U3nZx","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":25170,"input":9696,"output":253,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15221}},"cost":0}}
