{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884712382,"sessionID":"ses_285064a34ffeQXA6kTt14U3nZx","part":{"id":"prt_d7afa3411001EZlT88xsDJcyqB","messageID":"msg_d7afa17d9001x7YyJb7yiKaKSZ","sessionID":"ses_285064a34ffeQXA6kTt14U3nZx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-fb6421ebea3f41378047058bf5c5dbfb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775884712367,"end":1775884712381}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884712393,"sessionID":"ses_285064a34ffeQXA6kTt14U3nZx","part":{"id":"prt_d7afa35d3001ldjfoj7FtdWGQR","messageID":"msg_d7afa17d9001x7YyJb7yiKaKSZ","sessionID":"ses_285064a34ffeQXA6kTt14U3nZx","type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"toolu_tool-112d6d676cb14279851fb7350a468635","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"manifests/charts/base/templates/*.yaml"},"output":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml","metadata":{"count":4,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z","time":{"start":1775884712371,"end":1775884712391}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884712397,"sessionID":"ses_285064a34ffeQXA6kTt14U3nZx","part":{"id":"prt_d7afa3995001l5X0OfVIAaaDHJ","messageID":"msg_d7afa17d9001x7YyJb7yiKaKSZ","sessionID":"ses_285064a34ffeQXA6kTt14U3nZx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f1c6270bde69407ba6ad12b9ac978af7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-028 |\n8: | Module | sdk-python |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: Provide a Python SDK client (`AgentRuntimeClient`) for invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router. This client enables users to:\n17: \n18: 1. Bootstrap session IDs via GET request to the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint\n19: 2. Send JSON payloads to Agent Runtime workloads with session header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n20: 3. Manage client lifecycle via context manager protocol\n21: 4. Configure timeouts and connection pooling for HTTP requests\n22: \n23: This is the second public client class exported from the `agentcube` package, complementing `CodeInterpreterClient` for code interpreter sessions.\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n28: \n29: ### 2.1 In Scope\n30: \n31: - `AgentRuntimeClient` class implementation with:\n32:   - Constructor accepting `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`\n33:   - Context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`)\n34:   - `invoke(payload, timeout)` method for sending JSON payloads\n35:   - `close()` method for closing HTTP session\n36:   - Session ID bootstrapping via GET request when `session_id` not provided\n37: \n38: - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class implementation with:\n39:   - Constructor accepting `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `pool_connections`, `pool_maxsize`\n40:   - `bootstrap_session_id()` method for GET request to invocation endpoint\n41:   - `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout)` method for POST request\n42:   - `close()` method for closing HTTP session\n43:   - Class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n44: \n45: - Update `agentcube/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeClient`\n46: - Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n47: - Unit tests for both client classes\n48: \n49: ### 2.2 Out of Scope\n50: \n51: - Control plane session management (handled by `ControlPlaneClient`)\n52: - Code interpreter operations (handled by `CodeInterpreterClient`)\n53: - Retry logic or circuit breaker patterns\n54: - Async API support\n55: - Authentication token handling on data plane (Router handles JWT)\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n60: \n61: ### 3.1 新增文件\n62: \n63: | File | Description |\n64: |------|-------------|\n65: | `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` public client class |\n66: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` internal HTTP client |\n67: | `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | Unit tests for AgentRuntimeClient |\n68: \n69: ### 3.2 修改文件\n70: \n71: | File | Change |\n72: |------|--------|\n73: | `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py` | Add export of `AgentRuntimeClient` to `__all__` |\n74: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Add export of `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n75: \n76: ### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n77: \n78: | Dependency | Purpose |\n79: |------------|---------|\n80: | `requests` | HTTP client library (already in pyproject.toml) |\n81: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` for connection pooling |\n82: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` for logging |\n83: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy (not actively raised by AgentRuntimeClient) |\n84: \n85: ### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n86: \n87: | Consumer | Usage |\n88: |----------|-------|\n89: | End users | Invoke Agent Runtime workloads via SDK |\n90: | Example scripts | `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py` (optional) |\n91: | Integration tests | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` (optional extension) |\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n96: \n97: ### Alternative 1: Single unified client\n98: \n99: Combine `AgentRuntimeClient` and `CodeInterpreterClient` into a single `AgentCubeClient` with mode switching.\n100: \n101: **Rejected:** Different lifecycle semantics. CodeInterpreter requires control plane session creation/deletion; AgentRuntime only bootstraps session via data plane GET. Separate clients provide cleaner APIs.\n102: \n103: ### Alternative 2: Async-first API\n104: \n105: Implement async/await based client using `aiohttp`.\n106: \n107: **Rejected:** SDK currently uses synchronous `requests` library. Adding async would double the API surface and require new dependency. Async support can be added in future AR if needed.\n108: \n109: ### Alternative 3: Session ID passed directly to invoke\n110: \n111: Require users to call `bootstrap_session_id()` manually and pass session_id to each `invoke()`.\n112: \n113: **Rejected:** UX would be poor. Client should manage session lifecycle transparently, similar to `CodeInterpreterClient` pattern.\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ## 5. Risks\n118: \n119: | Risk | Mitigation |\n120: |------|------------|\n121: | Router URL required but not provided | Raise `ValueError` with clear message, same pattern as CodeInterpreterClient |\n122: | Session header missing in bootstrap response | Raise `ValueError` with message \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\" |\n123: | Invoke called without valid session_id | Raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` |\n124: | Connection pool exhaustion | Use configurable pool size defaults (pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10) |\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n129: \n130: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n131: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` in `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n132: - [ ] Update `agentcube/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeClient`\n133: - [ ] Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` to export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n134: - [ ] Write unit tests for `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n135: - [ ] Write unit tests for `AgentRuntimeClient`\n136: - [ ] Verify timeout tuple semantics: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n137: - [ ] Verify session header handling: `x-agentcube-session-id`\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 7. References\n142: \n143: - python-sdk/design.md — AgentCube Python SDK design\n144: - python-sdk/spec.md — SDK specification with AgentRuntime requirements\n145: - agentcube/code_interpreter.py — Reference implementation pattern\n146: - agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py — Reference data plane client\n\n(End of file - total 146 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-028 |\n| Module | sdk-python |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nProvide a Python SDK client (`AgentRuntimeClient`) for invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router. This client enables users to:\n\n1. Bootstrap session IDs via GET request to the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint\n2. Send JSON payloads to Agent Runtime workloads with session header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n3. Manage client lifecycle via context manager protocol","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775884712373,"end":1775884712394}}}}
